## Summary

This room covers the fundamentals of digital forensics — the branch of forensics that investigates cyber crimes. The practical exercise involved analyzing a ransom letter PDF and an image file using forensic tools (pdfinfo and exiftool) to extract metadata and identify the author, location, and camera model used by the kidnapper.

## Tools Used

- `pdfinfo` — extract PDF metadata
- `exiftool` — extract image EXIF data including GPS coordinates
- Google Maps — convert GPS coordinates to street name

